This year, Mardi Gras looked very different since I received my new additional title of ‘mama’. I had to pack goldfish, blankets and noise canceling headphones instead of just mixers for adult beverages. Luckily, I have a pretty good support system. Women empowerment is something that has been on the forefront in recent times. I don’t always feel that it’s authentic though. Sometimes it’s just for the optics. 

My newest experience with a woman led management team has been absolutely amazing! My manager’s main focus is making us feel seen and valued as women. She advocates for her clients beyond expectations. I couldn’t feel more appreciated and centered than I do with @isabellamastrodicasa of @neversettlemedia 
She’s not here just for the numbers, she wants to see the best for us all. 

I’m here to cheer her on; as well as the other ladies of @neversettlemedia (not all pictured)! It’s all authentic love over here! 🥰🥳😘

It takes a lot of energy to hang with my girls, but my time with them is always much-needed! I like to connect with myself before a big weekend full of socializing. With being a wife and mom, it’s hard sometimes to get alone time, but I have to prioritize my self-care so that I’m my best for everyone.
Getting ready for Essence Festival of Culture, I like to plan out which booths I want to go to. My Be Rooted Co. Journal is perfect for that and also affirming myself to protect my energy for the weekend ahead. Paired with the Elevation set of two gold pens from the Tina Wells stationery collection gives me a chic feel while journaling. Setting intentions for my time at Essence Festival isn’t complete without the fresh and inspiring palette of the Satya + Sage ‘Goddess’ candle. I like being able to dive into my skincare regimen with The Lip Bar’s Makeup Remover Balm. It is perfect for giving my face a jumpstart by removing all makeup and deep cleansing the skin underneath to highlight my summer glow. I also love bathing with Shea Moisture Black Soap Body Wash. Made with fair trade shea butter, coconut, shea, and palm oils, it leaves my skin feeling so soft. It’s very soothing and I’m instantly ready for a good night’s rest before the festivities that await.

These Black-owned products are essential items for Essence! Head over to target.com to get ready for this year’s Essence Festival of Culture! @target @essence #ad

This past month has reminded me to be grateful for the things I’m currently experiencing. I’m in the season that I prayed for and have to take the time to stop and reflect on how truly blessed I am.

This year, my mom asked me what I’m looking forward to in this new year of life. I had been thinking a lot about this notion leading up to my birthday. 

My plan is to lean more into knowing I am worthy of all things good. I don’t have to prove it to anyone. I am a divine recipient of God’s blessings and I am worthy of receiving them. I can release the need for people pleasing because it is not serving me. 

My blessings have already happened. I’m simply watching it all unfold. 

Cheers to 33(3) ✨🤲🏾🥳

We put a lot of thought into these designs and feel really proud of the results! Throughout our developing journey of motherhood we kept finding ourselves frustrated with the clothing available for women. Loungewear would be cute and comfy but never functional. This line is for everyone but we put special thought for all the mamas!

This pump will hopefully allow for that because it’s not as daunting as other pumps that I’ve used before. This one really gets the job done! It has 12 levels and I only go up to 4 but still get so much milk out in under 20min. 
Check out @thesucklecenter for more info on the pump I’m using. 

Feel free to ask me any questions you have about breastfeeding or pumping!

[2] Wearable/hands free pumps

Postpartum Check in 🥹 This current postpartum season has definitely had its highs and lows already. I’m working through them by feeling deeply and asking my village for support. Almost to the 4 week mark and ya girl is alright. Physically, I’ve been feeling great! Mentally, I’ve had some outside opinions allow self doubt to creep in. I’m working on affirming myself to avoid looking for outside validation. It’s an ongoing process but I’m growing and thriving right along with my newborn son. 

Check on your postpartum friends! That’s anyone with a child under 7 😉 Love yall!

Voiceover words by @thehealher 🤎 (cover photo)

Becoming a family of 4 has been DEEP! We’ve definitely been enjoying all the snuggles with Rai his first 4 weeks with us. He enjoys long rests in our arms and warm breastmilk. Lol Reign is totally obsessed with his little brother and hates to see him cry. 🥹

Between RSV in the home and attempting to have solo time with both kids and parents we are definitely grateful for our village. We’ve had family and friends help us in different ways and we have been very appreciative. 

Send us some love and light as we get stronger as a family going into this second month 🤎🫶🏾🤗
